## Running the Pre-trained ACCLIP Model on KITTI

To run the pre-trained ACCLIP model on the KITTI test set, use the provided `run_kitti.sh` script with the following command:

```bash
sh ./run_kitti.sh \
  path/to/weight/*.pth \
  /path/to/kitti_test.csv \
  /path/to/images/ \
  20


Arguments

Model weights: Path to the .pth file containing the trained model

Test CSV: Path to the kitti_test.csv file with test sequences

Output directory: Directory where predictions and logs will be saved

Number of predictions: How many future frames to predict (e.g., 10)
